                    <li>I plugged in too many MCP servers at once — context window filled with tool descriptions, agent got slower and less accurate. Lesson: if you are not actively using an MCP server, turn it off. 😳</li>
                    <li>I used GitHub MCP for a simple <code>gh repo view</code> — loaded 55,000 tokens to do a two-second CLI task. The agent worked fine. The overhead was absurd.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
